The paper deals with Neural Architecture Search (NAS), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The experiments are conducted on image classification tasks, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the proposed framework is generally applicable and can be integrated into existing optimizers, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of data and the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the optimization of neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
